Faure
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1557,1764]" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">
This genus comprises only two species which are reported from Africa and Asia (
<bibRefCitation accessDate="2019-05-01" author="ThripsWiki" box="[1072,1271,1557,1583]" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" publicationUrl="http://thrips.info/wiki/" refId="ref7542" refString="ThripsWiki (2019) providing information on the World's thrips. Available from: http: // thrips. info / wiki / (accessed 1 May 2019)" title="providing information on the World's thrips" type="url" year="2019">ThripsWiki 2019</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Faure" box="[1290,1436,1557,1584]" firstAuthor="Faure" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref6172" refString="Faure, J. C. (1933) New genera and species of Thysanoptera from South Africa. Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society, 28, 1 - 20." type="journal article" year="1933">Faure (1933)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Faure" authorityYear="1933" box="[268,362,1593,1619]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Idiothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellus">
<emphasis box="[268,362,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">I. bellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[436,584,1593,1619]" name="South Africa" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, and this species was subsequently reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[1168,1226,1593,1619]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">India</collectingCountry>
(Ananthakrishnan 1964) and then from 
<collectingRegion box="[399,601,1629,1656]" country="Iran" name="Kerman" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Kerman province</collectingRegion>
, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[721,766,1630,1656]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kheyrandish Koshkoei" box="[783,1117,1629,1655]" firstAuthor="Kheyrandish Koshkoei" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" refId="ref6423" refString="Kheyrandish Koshkoei, M. (2000) Faunistic survey of Thysanoptera in Kerman and study of population density of active species on rose. M. Sc. Thesis, College of Agriculture, Tarbiat Modarres University, Tehran, Iran, 137 pp. [In Persian with English summary]" type="book" year="2000">Kheyrandish Koshkoei 2000</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Minaei" box="[1138,1302,1629,1655]" firstAuthor="Minaei" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" pagination="279 - 290" refId="ref6523" refString="Minaei, K. (2013) The Phlaeothrips - lineage of fungus feeding thrips (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripidae) in Iran with a new species of Hindsiothrips. Zootaxa, 3599 (3), 279 - 290. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3599.3.5" type="journal article" year="2013">Minaei (2013)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Faure" authorityYear="1933" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Idiothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bellus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">I. bellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[235,304,1665,1691]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[202,1383,184,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[197,1390,179,1862]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Fungus feeding thrips species of Iran (1) Hindsiothrips sisakhti (female); (2) Idiothrips bellus (female); (3) Hoplandrothrips bidens (female); (4) Liophloeothrips arganicus (female); (5) Hoplothrips (female); (6) Cephalothrips monilicornis (female); (7) Cephalothrips coxalis (female); (8) Allothrips bournieri (female); (9) Stictothrips farsi sp. n. (female); (10) Stictothrips farsi sp. n. (male); (11) Pseudocryptothrips meridionalis (female); (12) Megathrips flavipes (female)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3364946/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) in 
<collectingRegion box="[351,508,1665,1692]" country="Iran" name="Fars" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Fars province</collectingRegion>
, and one female has been collected from leaf litter of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1126,1220,1666,1692]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1126,1220,1666,1692]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. The only other species in the genus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="zur Strassen" authorityYear="1968" box="[387,555,1701,1727]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Idiothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maghrebinus">
<emphasis box="[387,555,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">I. maghrebinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains known from a single female taken in flowers of 
<taxonomicName box="[1193,1436,1701,1727]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Oleaceae" genus="Phillyrea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustifolia">
<emphasis box="[1193,1436,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Phillyrea angustifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at Asni, 
<collectingCountry box="[244,345,1738,1764]" name="Morocco" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">Morocco</collectingCountry>
(zur 
<bibRefCitation author="Strassen, R." box="[404,564,1737,1764]" journalOrPublisher="Abhandlungen der senckenbergischen naturforschenden Gesellschaft" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" pagination="1 - 125" part="15" refId="ref7622" refString="zur Strassen, R. (1968) Okologische und zoogeographische Studien uber die-Fransenflugler-Fauna (Ins., Thysanoptera) des sudlichen-Marokko. Abhandlungen der senckenbergischen naturforschenden Gesellschaft, 15, 1 - 125." title="Okologische und zoogeographische Studien uber die-Fransenflugler-Fauna (Ins., Thysanoptera) des sudlichen-Marokko" type="journal article" year="1968">Strassen 1968</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
